Chairman of Association of Local Governments of Nigeria (ALGON) in Plateau State Ezekiel Vuelgap, on Thursday said striking local government workers and teachers in the state would be paid their new minimum wage salaries. Vuelgap, who spoke to reporters in Jos said before the close of work today (Thursday), most LGA workers would receive alerts for their salaries. I appeal to the striking workers to call off the strike and resume work immediately as soon as they are paid. He said the Simon Lalong-led administration is determined to better the lives of citizens. Vuelgap, who is also the Chairman of Mikang Local Government Area of Plateau State further said: â€œI commend Governor Simon Lalong for the prevailing industrial harmony he has with workers since he assumed duty as Plateau State Governor.